📁 Task 1 – Create Your Workflow Directory

From your project root:

mkdir -p .github/workflows

Create the workflow:

nano .github/workflows/ci.yml
⚙️ Task 2 – Create Your First CI Pipeline
name: DevOps CI Pipeline

on:
  push:
    branches:
      - main

  pull_request:
    branches:
      - main

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest

    steps:
      - name: Checkout Code
        uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Show System Information
        run: |
          echo "Hostname: $(hostname)"
          echo "User: $USER"
          uname -a

      - name: Run Application
        run: |
          chmod +x app/app.sh
          ./app/app.sh

      - name: Run Tests
        run: |
          chmod +x app/test.sh
          ./app/test.sh
🛠️ Task 3 – Create Application

Create:

nano app/app.sh
#!/bin/bash

echo "DevOps Application Started"
echo "Application is running successfully"

Make executable:

chmod +x app/app.sh
🧪 Task 4 – Create Tests

Create:

nano app/test.sh
#!/bin/bash

echo "Running tests..."

if [ -f "app/app.sh" ]; then
    echo "PASS: Application file exists"
else
    echo "FAIL: Application file missing"
    exit 1
fi

echo "All tests passed"
